laboratory_examinations.findings: Extremely high plasma 17-estradiol level of 9476 pmol/L (normal range: 120-300 pmol/L) and elevated gonadotrophin levels (LH: 24 IU/L, FSH: 13 IU/L, normal ranges: LH: 2-8 IU/L, FSH: 2-10 IU/L)

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Progesterone, testosterone, and adrenal steroid evaluation
laboratory_examinations.findings: Elevated rates for progesterone, testosterone, androstenedione, and dihydrotestosterone; normal levels for adrenal steroids including aldosterone, cortisol, DHEA; very low SHBG (indicating absence of a hepatic effect of estrogen)
AMH level normal; significantly elevated levels for inhibin A (516 pg/mL, normal range: 10-90 pg/mL) and inhibin B (376 pg/mL, normal range: 60-195 pg/mL).

17-estradiol: 6771 pmol/L (normal range: 120-300 pmol/L); estrone: 6416 pmol/L (normal range: 65-400 pmol/L); testosterone: 3.5 nmol/L (normal range: 0.3-1.5 nmol/L); androstenedione: 18.5 nmol/L (normal range: 1.7-5.3 nmol/L); progesterone: 14.3 nmol/L (normal range: 0.3-6.5 nmol/L); low levels of inhibin A and B in brother with low testosterone.
